                            <comment id="16392195" author="varunthacker" created="Fri, 9 Mar 2018 00:58:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Amrit!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Uni-Directional :&#160;It&apos;s mandatory define the update processor chain on the target&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Bi-Directional&#160; :&#160;It&apos;s mandatory&#160;to define it on both source and target.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So removing this from the source in the uni-directional use-case will reduce 3-4 lines of copy pasting but the user might look at it as an inconsistency.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I know it will work without it so the changes are correct hence I&apos;m +0 for the change &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

